[8] Dysentery - Russia (Chuvashia)
Date: Sun, 16 Oct 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Itar-Tass [edited]
<http://www.itar-tass.com/eng/level2.html?NewsID=2524649&PageNum=0>

77 schoolchildren in the Chuvashia village of Vurnary proved to have
intestinal infection, and 56 of them are now in a hospital, the
Chuvashia Health and Social Development Ministry said on Sun, 16 Oct 2005.
According to the preliminary information, 48 children aging from 7
through 17 [years of age] have dysentery. Doctors say that their
condition is not critical. The school is under sanitary treatment.
One of the theories is that the children were poisoned with
[contaminated] sausage, so the school canteen is temporary closed.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
